## Education

- Ph.D. in Statistics, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. 2006--2011

- B.S. in Statistics, Seoul National University. 1999--2003


## Academic appointment

* Department of Statistics, Seoul National University 
     + Associate Professor, 2018--
     
* Department of Statistics, University of Pittsburgh
     + Associate Professor, 2017-2019.
     + Graduate Director, 2017--2018.
     + Assistant Professor, 2011--2017.

     
## Research Interest

- Modern Multivariate Statistics 
- Non-Euclidean data analysis
- High-dimension, low-sample-size (HDLSS) analysis
- Shape analysis 
- Data fusion
- Geometrically-constrained inference 

## Honors 

- Excellence in Teaching Award, College of Natural Science, SNU, Sep. 2019.
- Early Career Development Award, Korean International Statistical Society, 2016.
- US Junior Oberwolfach Fellow, MFO, Germany, 2014.
- Distinguished Paper Award, International Biometric Society/ENAR, 2011.
- Wassily Hoeffding Award, Statistics and Operations Research, University of North Carolina, 2007

## Grants

- PI, A grant for Basic Science and Future Technologies, Samsung Science & Technology Foundation.

- PI, NRF 2019R1A2C2002256, 2019-2024.

- PI, Internal grant, Seoul National University, 2018-2020.

- PI, dB-SERC, University of Pittsburgh,  2017-2018.

- PI, Central Research Development Fund, University of Pittsburgh, 2016-2018.

- PI, NSF DMS-1307178, 2013-2016.

- PI, Hewlett International Grants, UCIS, University of Pittsburgh, 2012, 2013, 2016.

- Co-I, NIH (NCI) 5R01CA159471-03 (PI: Michael Gach), 2011-2014.

